cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.LG 

This paper discusses the use of network intrusion detection systems in the context of the internet of things, which is a subfield of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also proposes a model-hybrid approach to generate synthetic datasets for training the IDS, which involves the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Finally, the paper addresses the challenges of collecting data in IoT systems, which is a topic related to social and information networks (cs.SI).
